00:13:07,661 --> 00:13:13,542
JUNG YI-HYUN

158
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:16,545
Here.

159
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:19,340
Hey, do you still want to play
baseball even with that knee?

160
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,717
I get paid to play for this team.

161
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,886
-What kind of a case is it?
-Murder.

162
00:13:23,969 --> 00:13:25,971
You didn't even know what the case was?

163
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:28,098
I was told to come, so I came.

164
00:13:28,182 --> 00:13:30,059
I even gave up my day off and my game.

165
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:32,520
-You should thank me.
-Oh, thank you so much.

166
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,980
People from the next room reported it.

167
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:36,732
-I heard the scream and--
-Excuse me.

168
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:39,276
-Who's the victim?
-The front desk employee.

169
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,194
Let's go.

170
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:42,905
-All I need to do is testify?
-I can't believe this.

171
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:13,227
What did they do to his neck?

172
00:14:15,020 --> 00:14:16,438
Well, that looks like

173
00:14:17,147 --> 00:14:19,191
it was done with a dull blade, right?

174
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,818
Perhaps they wanted him to suffer.

175
00:14:20,901 --> 00:14:23,696
-Who's the suspect?
-The guest who stayed here.

176
00:14:23,779 --> 00:14:26,240
There were a lot of complaints
because he was so noisy.

177
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:28,909
But who covered him with this?

178
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:37,084
-Did you meddle with the crime scene?
-No, we didn't touch anything.

179
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:39,378
-Any witnesses?
-None so far.

180
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:42,506
He said it was like this from the start.

181
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:46,802
Did they check the security cams?

182
00:14:46,885 --> 00:14:48,387
Right. The security cams.

183
00:14:53,058 --> 00:14:54,852
Hey, what about the security cams?

184
00:14:56,103 --> 00:15:00,190
They're checking it now,
but they can't find the suspect leaving.

185
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:04,737
He covered the victim's face and ran away.

186
00:15:06,905 --> 00:15:08,741
But the camera didn't catch him leaving.

187
00:15:08,824 --> 00:15:12,036
I'm sure he did
an electronic access register,

188
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:13,829
but the CDSCHQ won't let us see it.

189
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:16,206
It's a breach
of personal information protection.

190
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:17,875
Hey, killers have no rights.

191
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:21,003
They should integrate
the information and arrest all of them.

192
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:22,838
I don't understand.

193
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,260
Oh, I didn't mean you.

194
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,470
Okay.

195
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:36,685
I'm sure they didn't
search in there, right?

196
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:54,328
Hey, I know you investigate recklessly,
hoping for good luck, but--

197
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:56,997
It can't even go near the "reckless" part.

198
00:15:57,539 --> 00:16:01,293
I know someone who's even more…

199
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:04,505
Sir…

200
00:16:05,839 --> 00:16:07,091
come out.

201
00:16:07,174 --> 00:16:08,175
Are you kidding me?

202
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:12,012
If this is another joke,
I'm going to kill you today.

203
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:17,267
Damn it!

204
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:18,936
Our eyes just met.

205
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:22,856
Hey, we got the culprit. Don't come in.

206
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:24,984
Come in later.

207
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:35,160
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD, SUNG WOO-JAE

208
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,496
Did you do this, Mr. Sung Woo-jae?

209
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:39,707
I don't know.

210
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:44,461
Did you cover the body
because you were scared to see the body?

211
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:46,797
Then why did you kill him?

212
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,298
You don't remember that either?

213
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:53,512
I had a dream, but…

214
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:56,765
Was the dream about killing him?

215
00:16:59,893 --> 00:17:02,771
You’re covered in blood,
so you couldn't run away.

216
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:07,067
You were panicking, but the police came,
so you must've hidden.

217
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,194
By the way, where's the weapon?

218
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:12,573
What did you kill him with in the dream?

219
00:17:12,656 --> 00:17:14,616
Oh, that's right.

220
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:17,369
The court won't acknowledge it
if there's no weapon.

221
00:17:20,748 --> 00:17:22,249
You see,

222
00:17:22,332 --> 00:17:25,210
I was thirsty for some reason, so…

223
00:17:37,264 --> 00:17:38,682
Did you bite him?

224
00:17:47,691 --> 00:17:49,026
Give me one more.

225
00:17:52,946 --> 00:17:54,281
ONE MAIN SIDE DISH PER PERSON

226
00:18:05,459 --> 00:18:07,920
Were you doing physical labor or what?

227
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:10,005
Why are you eating so much?

228
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:12,925
I'm upset, so don't say anything.

229
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:16,637
Here.

230
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:20,682
If you have something to say, go ahead.

231
